revisions.description: a) Modified to have characters/line to be less than 72 and add range for Integer32. b) Modified to use cwspConfigGrp3 in ciscoWANSvcMIBCompliance3.

a) Added 'cwspRoutingPriority' object in cwspConfigTable. b) The DEFVAL clause for 'cwspUniVersion' and 'cwspNniVersion' is changed to 'unsupported(7)' from 'uni31'. The DESCRIPTION is modified for these objects.
The change is to back out previous revision. The requirement was changed.
The change is to use 'unsupoerted(7)' as default for both 'cwspUniVersion' and 'cwspNniVersion'. DESCRIPTION modified for both variables as well.
The change is to add 'self(9)' enumeration to 'cwspUniVersion'. This value is used to indicate a voice port.

The changes are as follows: (1) Add one mib variable 'cwspConnTraceLastNode'. (2) Add 'unsupported(7)'to 'cwspNniVersion' variable. (3) Add additional comments in DESCRIPTION of 'cwspNniVersion' and 'cwspUniVersion' variables. (4) Corrected spelling error.
The changes are as follows: (1) Description for 'ENNI' is added. (2) cwspNniVersion -- enumeration enni(4) and aini(5) are added. (3) cwspOperNniSigVersion -- enumeration aini(5) is added.
The changes are as follows: (1) The default value of cwspMinSvccVci is changed to 35. (2) The lower range of cwspMaxSvccVci changed to 35.
Importing symbol stratacom from CISCOWAN-SMI instead from BASIS-MIB.

The changes are as follows. (1) The lower bound and upper bound of the following MIB objects has been changed from 0 to 1 and from 100 to 200 respectively. (i) cwspUtilFactorCbr (ii) cwspUtilFactorRtVbr (iii) cwspUtilFactorNrtVbr (iv) cwspUtilFactorAbr (v) cwspUtilFactorUbr (2) The lower bound of cwspMinSvccVci object has been changed from 32 to 0.
This is the initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoWANSvcMIB.description: The MIB modules describe an ATM network service on a BPX-SES or a MGX ATM switch. This MIB module provides configuring, provisioning, as well as status gathering for ATM services. Abbreviation used: ABR -- Available Bit Rate AINI -- ATM Inter-Network Interface ATM -- Asynchronous Transfer Mode BGN -- Begin BW -- Bandwidth CBR -- Constant Bit Rate ENNI -- Enhanced Network to Network Interface Note: The 'ENNI' term used here indicating 'enhanced' or 'friendly' NNI for linking two networks of CISCO AutoRoute or PNNI switches. The XPVCs and XPVPs are provisioned across them. Functionality includes changing segment OAM cell handling so that these cells flow over 'end-to-end OAM segment' loops for the provisioned length of the XPVC or XPVP, i.e. the 'segment' comprises the two or three segments between the user ports. Also implemented at ENNIs is an LMI functionality that enables auto-discovery of the ENNIs. ER -- Error Recovery GAT -- Generic Application Transport IE -- Information Element IISP -- Interim Inter-Switch Signaling Protocol ILMI -- Interim Local Management Interface MD -- Management Data PNNI -- Private Network-Network Interface RS -- Resynchronization REJ -- Rejection SD -- Sequence Data SDP -- Sequence Data with Poll SPVC -- Soft Permanent Virtual Circuit SSCOP -- Service Specific Connection Oriented Protocol SVC -- Switched Virtual Circuit UBR -- Unspecified Bit Rate UD -- Unit Data UNI -- User-Network Interface USTAT -- Unsolicited STAT VBR -- Variable Bit Rate

cwspSigCfgT301.name: cwspSigCfgT301
cwspSigCfgT301.description: Timer started when ALERT message received at Call Received State. Normally, timer is stopped when CONNECT message is received. Clear call at first expiry.

cwspSigCfgT303.name: cwspSigCfgT303
cwspSigCfgT303.description: Timer started when SETUP message sent at Call Present State. Normally, timer is stopped when ALERT, CONNECT, RELEASE COMPLETE or CALL PROCEEDING message is received. Resend SETUP message and restart the timer at first expiry; Clear network connection and enter NULL state at second expiry.

cwspSigCfgT308.name: cwspSigCfgT308
cwspSigCfgT308.description: Timer started when RELEASE message sent at Release Indication State. Normally, timer is stopped when RELEASE COMPLETE or RELEASE message is received. Resend RELEASE and restart the timer at first expiry; Release call reference and enter NULL state at second expiry.

cwspSigCfgT310.name: cwspSigCfgT310
cwspSigCfgT310.description: Timer started when CALL PROCEEDING message received at Incoming Call Proceeding State. Normally, timer is stopped when ALERT, CONNECT or RELEASE message is received. Clear call at first expiry. Range from 10 to 20 seconds for UNI 3.0/3.1 with default of 10; 30 to 120 seconds for UNI 4.0 with default of 30, default number can be 10 or 30, 10 is used.

cwspSigCfgT316.name: cwspSigCfgT316
cwspSigCfgT316.description: Timer started when RESTART message sent Restart Request State. Normally, timer is stopped when RESTART ACK message is received. RESTART may be sent multiple times in both first or second expiry.

cwspSigCfgT317.name: cwspSigCfgT317
cwspSigCfgT317.description: Timer started when RESTART message received at Restart State. Normally, timer is stopped when Internal clearing of call references happen. Maintenance notification at first expiry. The value of this timer should be less than T316.

cwspSigCfgT322.name: cwspSigCfgT322
cwspSigCfgT322.description: Timer started when STATUS ENQUIRY message sent at any call state. Normally, timer is stopped when STATUS RELEASE or RELEASE COMPLETE message is received. STATUS ENQUIREY message may be resent several times in both first or second expiry.

cwspSigCfgT397.name: cwspSigCfgT397
cwspSigCfgT397.description: Timer started when ALERTING or PARTY ALERTING message received in point-to-multipoint call. Normally timer is stopped when ADD PARTY ACK message is received. Clear party at first expiry.

cwspSigCfgT398.name: cwspSigCfgT398
cwspSigCfgT398.description: Timer is started when DROP PARTY message sent at Drop Party Initiated State. Normally, timer is stopped when DROP PARTY ACK or RELEASE message is received. Send DROP PARTY ACK or RELEASE at first expiry.

cwspSigCfgT399.name: cwspSigCfgT399
cwspSigCfgT399.description: Timer is started when ADD PARTY message sent at Add Party Initiated State. Normally, timer is stopped when ADD PARTY ACK, ADD PARTY REJ or RELEASE message is received. Clear the party and enter NULL Party State at first expiry. Range from 14 to 28 seconds for UNI 3.0/3.1 with default of 14; 34 to 124 seconds for UNI 4.0 with default of 34, default can be 14 or 34, 14 is used.

cwspMaxVciBits.name: cwspMaxVciBits

cwspUniVersion.name: cwspUniVersion
cwspUniVersion.description: An indication of the latest version of the ATM Forum UNI Signaling Specification that is supported on this ATM Interface. If this value is not present, a version of the UNI earlier than 3.1 is supported. The value of 'self(9)' indicates this entry is a voice port. If the peer IME's value of this object is the same as, or later than the local IME's value, then the version corresponding to the local IME's value should be attempted. Otherwise, if the peer IME's value of this object is earlier, and supported locally, then the local IME should attempt the version corresponding to the peer IME's value. Otherwise, compatibility of the two IMEs cannot be assumed.

cwspNniVersion.name: cwspNniVersion
cwspNniVersion.description: An indication of the latest version of the ATM Forum PNNI Signaling Specification that is supported on this ATM Interface. Note that the PNNI routing version is not determined through ILMI. If the peer IME's value of this object is the same as, or later than the local IME's value, then the version corresponding to the local IME's value should be attempted. Otherwise, if the peer IME's value of this object is earlier, and supported locally, then the local IME should attempt the version corresponding to the peer IME's value. Otherwise, compatibility of the two IMEs cannot be assumed.

cwspSide.name: cwspSide

This object is used in automatic ATM Interface-Type determination procedure such that a correct operational ATM Interface-type can be determined. An ATM End System shall take the value of user(1), and an ATM network node shall take the value of node(2).

cwspMaxP2mpRoots.name: cwspMaxP2mpRoots
cwspMaxP2mpRoots.description: Indicates the maximum number of root VCs (for point-to-multipoint) allowed on the interface.

cwspMaxP2mpLeafs.name: cwspMaxP2mpLeafs
cwspMaxP2mpLeafs.description: Indicates the maximum number of leaf VCs (for point-to-multipoint) allowed on the interface.

cwspMinSvccVpi.name: cwspMinSvccVpi
cwspMinSvccVpi.description: Indicates the minimum SVCC VPI configured on the interface.

cwspMaxSvccVpi.name: cwspMaxSvccVpi
cwspMaxSvccVpi.description: Indicates the maximum SVCC VPI configured on the interface.

cwspMinSvccVci.name: cwspMinSvccVci
cwspMinSvccVci.description: Indicates the minimum SVCC VCI configured on the interface.

cwspMaxSvccVci.name: cwspMaxSvccVci
cwspMaxSvccVci.description: Indicates the maximum SVCC VCI configured on the interface.

cwspMinSvpcVpi.name: cwspMinSvpcVpi
cwspMinSvpcVpi.description: Indicates the minimum SVPC VPI configured on the interface.

cwspMaxSvpcVpi.name: cwspMaxSvpcVpi
cwspMaxSvpcVpi.description: Indicates the maximum SVPC VPI configured on the interface.

cwspEnhancedIisp.name: cwspEnhancedIisp
cwspEnhancedIisp.description: Indicates whether the enhanced features for IISP are enabled or disabled.

cwspConfigTableRowStatus.name: cwspConfigTableRowStatus
cwspConfigTableRowStatus.description: Used to create and delete the Interface. However, only createAndGo, destroy, active and notInService are supported. NMS should only use createAndGo to create a row and destroy to delete a row. The managed device will either return active or notInService for a row status.

cwspAddrPlanSupported.name: cwspAddrPlanSupported
cwspAddrPlanSupported.description: The ATM address plan supported on an interface. This can only be modified if interface is public UNI. For all other interfaces, the value is aesa.

cwspIlmiSecureLink.name: cwspIlmiSecureLink
cwspIlmiSecureLink.description: Indicates whether ILMI Secure Link Protocol is enabled or disabled. When secure link protocol is enabled, loss in ILMI connectivity is treated as loss of attachment point which results in all SVCs/SVPs being released on the interface.

cwspIlmiAttachmentPoint.name: cwspIlmiAttachmentPoint
cwspIlmiAttachmentPoint.description: Indicates whether detection of loss of attachment procedures are enabled on this interface. When set to true, then standard ILMI procedures are employed to detect loss of attachment point. If set to false, then ILMI protocol on the interface does not detect the loss of attachment.

cwspIlmiLocalAttrStd.name: cwspIlmiLocalAttrStd
cwspIlmiLocalAttrStd.description: Indicates whether on modification of local attributes, procedures as recommended by ILMI 4.0 specification are followed or cisco proprietery procedures are followed. When set to true, the standard ILMI procedures are followed.

cwspIlmiUCSMEnable.name: cwspIlmiUCSMEnable
cwspIlmiUCSMEnable.description: Indicates whether ILMI user connection status monitoring is enabled or disabled.

cwspRoutingPriority.name: cwspRoutingPriority
cwspRoutingPriority.description: This object is the routing priority to be assigned to connections which enter the network from this ingress interface, but does not carry the routing priority signaling in the SETUP message. SETUP message. A default routing priority of 8 is used if this object is not configured. A routing priority 1 is the highest priority for a user connection. A connection tagged with a routing priority of 1 is derouted ahead of connections tagged with other priority values.

cwspSpvcAddress.name: cwspSpvcAddress
cwspSpvcAddress.description: This object identifies the internal NSAP assigned to a port by the switch. a) The format is that of 13-byte node prefix and 7-byte port number. b) When the switch's node prefix is modified, the node prefix part of this variable is also changed accordingly. Note: the switch's node prefix cannot be changed if there are connections on the switch. c) The port number can be physical port identifier or the ifIndex of this port.

cwspCallStatsTable.name: cwspCallStatsTable
cwspCallStatsTable.description: This Table contains objects showing the Statistics for SVC/SPVC calls on a given interface.

cwspCallStatsEntry.name: cwspCallStatsEntry
cwspCallStatsEntry.description: An entry contains SVC/SPVC call statistics

cwspCountReset.name: cwspCountReset
cwspCountReset.description: Writing a 2 to this object resets all counters.

cwspInCallAttempts.name: cwspInCallAttempts
cwspInCallAttempts.description: This object shows the number of incoming Signaling messages (Setup and Add Party) received by the switching node on this interface for Call establishment.

cwspInCallEstabs.name: cwspInCallEstabs
cwspInCallEstabs.description: This object shows the number of incoming Signaling Messages (Connect and Add Party Ack) received by the switching node on this interface which marks that a call has been successfully established.

cwspInCallFailures.name: cwspInCallFailures
cwspInCallFailures.description: This object shows the total number of incoming Point-to-Point (p2p) and Point-to-MultiPoint(p2mp) SVC/SPVC call attempts failed on this interface.

cwspInFilterFailures.name: cwspInFilterFailures
cwspInFilterFailures.description: This object shows the number of incoming Point-to-Point(p2p) and Point-to-MultiPoint(p2mp) SVC/SPVC call attempts which failed due to address filtering on this interface.

cwspInRouteFailures.name: cwspInRouteFailures
cwspInRouteFailures.description: This object shows the number of incoming Point-to-Point(p2p) and Point-to-MulitPoint(p2mp) SVC/SPVC call attempts on this interface which failed because there was no route to the destination available.

cwspInResrcFailures.name: cwspInResrcFailures
cwspInResrcFailures.description: This object shows the number of incoming Point-to-Point(p2p) and Point-to-MulitPoint(p2mp) SVC/SPVC call attempts on this interface which failed because there were not enough resources as requested in the parameters of the call.

cwspInTimerFailures.name: cwspInTimerFailures
cwspInTimerFailures.description: This object shows the number of signaling timers timed out for incoming Point-to-Point(p2p) and Point-to-MultiPoint(p2mp) SVC/SPVC calls on this interface.

cwspInCrankbacks.name: cwspInCrankbacks
cwspInCrankbacks.description: This object shows the number of Crankback IEs received on this interface for incoming Point-to-Point(p2p) and Point-to-MultiPoint (p2mp) SVC/SPVC call attempts.

cwspOutCallAttempts.name: cwspOutCallAttempts
cwspOutCallAttempts.description: This object shows the number of outgoing Signaling messages (Setup and Add Party) on this interface for Call establishment.

cwspOutCallEstabs.name: cwspOutCallEstabs
cwspOutCallEstabs.description: This object shows the number of outgoing Signaling messages (Connect and Add Party Ack) which mark the call being established on this interface

cwspOutCallFailures.name: cwspOutCallFailures
cwspOutCallFailures.description: This object shows the total number of outgoing Signaling messages for Point-to-Point and Point-to-MultiPoint call establishment on this interface which failed.

cwspOutFilterFailures.name: cwspOutFilterFailures
cwspOutFilterFailures.description: This object shows the number of outgoing Signaling messages for call establishment on this interface which failed the address filtering.

cwspOutRouteFailures.name: cwspOutRouteFailures
cwspOutRouteFailures.description: This object shows the number of outgoing Signaling messages for call establishment on this interface which failed because the route was not available.

cwspOutResrcFailures.name: cwspOutResrcFailures
cwspOutResrcFailures.description: This object shows the number of outgoing Signaling messages for call establishment on this interface which failed because the resource requested was not available.

cwspOutTimerFailures.name: cwspOutTimerFailures
cwspOutTimerFailures.description: This object shows the number of Signaling timers timed-out on this interface for outgoing signaling messages.

cwspOutCrankbacks.name: cwspOutCrankbacks
cwspOutCrankbacks.description: This object shows the number of Crankback IEs being sent on this interface for outgoing signaling Release messages. This is generated on the node which generates the Crankback IEs.

cwspPrefixTable.name: cwspPrefixTable
cwspPrefixTable.description: A table specifying the network prefix(es) used for ILMI address registration.

cwspPrefixEntry.name: cwspPrefixEntry
cwspPrefixEntry.description: Information about a single network prefix contained in the prefix table.

cwspNetPrefix.name: cwspNetPrefix
cwspNetPrefix.description: The network prefix specified for use in ILMI address registration.

cwspPrefixRowStatus.name: cwspPrefixRowStatus
cwspPrefixRowStatus.description: Used to create, delete, activate and de-activate network prefixes used in ILMI address registration.

cwspAddressTable.name: cwspAddressTable
cwspAddressTable.description: The Interface ATM Address Table. This table contains all the attributes necessary to determine what the PNNI entity believes is reachable in terms of ATM End System Addresses and to determine which nodes are advertising this reachability. This table is also used to configure static routes to reachable addresses. Entries in this table can be created/deleted by setting the intfAddressRowStatus object to appropriate values. Existing entries in this table cannot be modified. Entries in this table can also be created/deleted through the command provided by the CLI.

cwspAddressEntry.name: cwspAddressEntry
cwspAddressEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a reachable address.

cwspAtmAddress.name: cwspAtmAddress
cwspAtmAddress.description: The value of the ATM End System Address.

cwspAddrLen.name: cwspAddrLen
cwspAddrLen.description: The address length in bits to be applied to the ATM End System Address.

cwspAddrType.name: cwspAddrType
cwspAddrType.description: The type of reachability from the advertising node to the address. This variable indicates either this ATM address ('internal') is a reachable ATM destination that is directly attached to the logical node advertising this address or an ATM address('exterior') that can be reached through a PNNI routing domain but which is not located in that routing domain.

cwspAddrProto.name: cwspAddrProto
cwspAddrProto.description: The routing mechanism via which the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable address was learned. A 'local' address indicates this address is automatically advertised. A 'static' address is not automatically advertised. By setting 'cwspAddrRedistribute' variable (see below) to 'true' will force a 'static' address to be advertised.

cwspAddrPlan.name: cwspAddrPlan
cwspAddrPlan.description: The address plan. For NSAP address, the first byte of the address automatically implies one of the three NSAP address plans: NSAP E.164, NSAP DCC or NSAP ICD.

cwspAddrScope.name: cwspAddrScope
cwspAddrScope.description: The PNNI scope of advertisement (i.e. level of PNNI hierarchy) of the reachability from the advertising node to the address.

cwspAddrRedistribute.name: cwspAddrRedistribute
cwspAddrRedistribute.description: Whether or not the reachable address specified by this entry is to be advertised by the local node into its PNNI routing domain. This object is only meaningful if the routing mechanism (cwspAddrProto) is static.

cwspAddressRowStatus.name: cwspAddressRowStatus
cwspAddressRowStatus.description: To create or delete a reachable address. Note that NMS should use CreateAndGo to create a row and Destroy to delete a row. The managed device will return active or notInService as row status.

cwspRegAddressTable.name: cwspRegAddressTable
cwspRegAddressTable.description: This table contains a list of ATM addresses that can be used for calls to and from a given interface by a switch or service. The ATM addresses are registered by the endsystem via ILMI. ILMI registered addresses cannot be deleted using this table. This table only applies to switches and network services.

cwspRegAddressEntry.name: cwspRegAddressEntry
cwspRegAddressEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Interface Registered Address table.

cwspRegAtmAddress.name: cwspRegAtmAddress
cwspRegAtmAddress.description: An address registered for a given switch or service interface.

cwspRegAddressOrgSscope.name: cwspRegAddressOrgSscope
cwspRegAddressOrgSscope.description: This object indicates the organizational scope for the referenced address. The information of the referenced address shall not be distributed outside the indicated scope. The default values for organizational scope are localNetwork(1) for ATM group addresses, and global(15) for individual addresses.

cwspCacConfigTable.name: cwspCacConfigTable
cwspCacConfigTable.description: A table specifying the CAC(Connection Admission Control) information for each interface.

cwspMaxBwCbr.description: This is the maximum bandwidth for CBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspMaxBwRtVbr.name: cwspMaxBwRtVbr
cwspMaxBwRtVbr.description: This is the maximum bandwidth for real time VBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspMaxBwUbr.name: cwspMaxBwUbr
cwspMaxBwUbr.description: This is the maximum bandwidth for UBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspMinBwCbr.description: This is the minimum bandwidth for CBR service in percentage. The total values of cwspMinBwCbr, cwspMinBwRtVbr, cwspMinBwNrtVbr, cwspMinBwAbr and cwspMinBwUbr can not exceed 1000000, i.e. 100%. cwspMinBwUbr.name: cwspMinBwUbr
cwspMinBwUbr.description: This is the minimum bandwidth for UBR service in percentage. The value for this variable is always 0.

cwspMaxVcCbr.description: This is the maximum number of VCs for CBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspMaxVcRtVbr.name: cwspMaxVcRtVbr
cwspMaxVcRtVbr.description: This is the maximum number of VCs for real time VBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspMaxVcNrtVbr.name: cwspMaxVcNrtVbr
cwspMaxVcNrtVbr.description: This is the maximum number of VCs for non-real time VBR service in percentage. The value of this variable is interpreted in the format of xxx.xxxx. For example a value of 750000 is interpreted as 75.0000%.

cwspLoadClr0RtVbr.name: cwspLoadClr0RtVbr
cwspLoadClr0RtVbr.description: The cell loss ratio-0 of real time VBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr0NrtVbr.name: cwspLoadClr0NrtVbr
cwspLoadClr0NrtVbr.description: The cell loss ratio-0 of non-real time VBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr0Abr.name: cwspLoadClr0Abr
cwspLoadClr0Abr.description: The cell loss ratio-0 of ABR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr0Ubr.name: cwspLoadClr0Ubr
cwspLoadClr0Ubr.description: The cell loss ratio-0 of UBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr01Cbr.name: cwspLoadClr01Cbr
cwspLoadClr01Cbr.description: The cell loss ratio-1 of CBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr01RtVbr.name: cwspLoadClr01RtVbr
cwspLoadClr01RtVbr.description: The cell loss ratio-1 of real time VBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr01NrtVbr.name: cwspLoadClr01NrtVbr
cwspLoadClr01NrtVbr.description: The cell loss ratio-1 of non-real time VBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr01Abr.name: cwspLoadClr01Abr
cwspLoadClr01Abr.description: The cell loss ratio-1 of ABR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadClr01Ubr.name: cwspLoadClr01Ubr
cwspLoadClr01Ubr.description: The cell loss ratio-1 of UBR service, -1 implies N/A.

cwspLoadMinGurCrCbr.name: cwspLoadMinGurCrCbr
cwspLoadMinGurCrCbr.description: The minimum guaranteed cell rate capacity of CBR service.

cwspLoadMinGurCrRtVbr.name: cwspLoadMinGurCrRtVbr
cwspLoadMinGurCrRtVbr.description: The minimum guaranteed cell rate capacity of real time VBR service.

cwspLoadMinGurCrNrtVbr.name: cwspLoadMinGurCrNrtVbr
cwspLoadMinGurCrNrtVbr.description: The minimum guaranteed cell rate capacity of non-real time VBR service.

cwspLoadMinGurCrAbr.name: cwspLoadMinGurCrAbr
cwspLoadMinGurCrAbr.description: The minimum guaranteed cell rate capacity of ABR service.

cwspLoadMinGurCrUbr.name: cwspLoadMinGurCrUbr
cwspLoadMinGurCrUbr.description: The minimum guaranteed cell rate capacity of UBR service.

cwspCallTable.name: cwspCallTable
cwspCallTable.description: This Table contains the objects which show parameters associated with a Point-to-Point(p2p) or Point-to-MultiPoint (p2mp) SVC/SPVC call.

cwspCallEntry.name: cwspCallEntry
cwspCallEntry.description: This object shows the multiple key index to get the Call record information. The key comprise of Interface Index, VPI/VCI value and Call Reference Value for the call.

cwspCallVpi.name: cwspCallVpi
cwspCallVpi.description: This object shows the VPI value of the call on this interface.

cwspCallVci.name: cwspCallVci
cwspCallVci.description: This object shows The VCI value of the call on this interface. The value should be in the range of 32-65535 (0=SPVP).

cwspCallLeafReference.name: cwspCallLeafReference
cwspCallLeafReference.description: This object shows the value of the Leaf Reference (EndPointReference) of the Call on this interface.

cwspCallCallRef.name: cwspCallCallRef
cwspCallCallRef.description: This object shows the Call Reference value of the call on this interface.

cwspCallCallingAddress.name: cwspCallCallingAddress
cwspCallCallingAddress.description: This object shows the Calling Party Address of the call.

cwspCallCalledAddress.name: cwspCallCalledAddress
cwspCallCalledAddress.description: This object shows the Called Party Address of the call.

cwspCallCallingSubAddr.name: cwspCallCallingSubAddr
cwspCallCallingSubAddr.description: This object shows the Calling Party Subaddress of the call.

cwspCallCalledSubAddr.name: cwspCallCalledSubAddr
cwspCallCalledSubAddr.description: This object shows the Called Party Subaddress of the call.

cwspCallOtherIntfIndex.name: cwspCallOtherIntfIndex
cwspCallOtherIntfIndex.description: This object shows the Other Interface of the call. Generally, this would be the outgoing/egress interface for the call.

cwspCallOtherIntfVpi.name: cwspCallOtherIntfVpi
cwspCallOtherIntfVpi.description: This object shows the VPI of the call on the partner interface.

cwspCallOtherIntfVci.name: cwspCallOtherIntfVci
cwspCallOtherIntfVci.description: This object shows The VCI of the call on the partner o interface. The value should be in the range of 32-65535 (0=SPVP).

cwspCallOtherIntfCallRef.name: cwspCallOtherIntfCallRef
cwspCallOtherIntfCallRef.description: This object shows the Call Reference of the call on the partner interface.

cwspCallType.name: cwspCallType
cwspCallType.description: This object shows the Call Type for the call on this interface. The call type could be SVC or SPVC.

cwspCallStartTime.name: cwspCallStartTime
cwspCallStartTime.description: This object shows the start time of the call. This is the timestamp when the Setup Message (or Add Party Message) was first received on this interface.

cwspCallBearerClass.name: cwspCallBearerClass
cwspCallBearerClass.description: This object shows the Bearer Class of the Call. It could be BcobA, BcobC, BcobX or VP Service

cwspCallServiceCategory.name: cwspCallServiceCategory
cwspCallServiceCategory.description: This object shows the service category of the call, which can be CBR, rtVBR, nrtVBR, ABR or UBR

cwspCallCastType.name: cwspCallCastType
cwspCallCastType.description: This object shows the Cast Type of the call, which can be a Point-to-Point (p2p), Point-to-MultiPoint (p2mp) or MultiPoint-to-Point (mp2p) call.

cwspCallClipSusceptibility.name: cwspCallClipSusceptibility
cwspCallClipSusceptibility.description: This object shows Susceptibility to Clipping. It can be susceptible or not susceptible.

cwspCallFwdConformance.name: cwspCallFwdConformance
cwspCallFwdConformance.description: This object shows the conformance of the call to the traffic sets in the forward direction. It can be CBR.1, CBR.2, CBR.3, VBR.1 VBR.2, VBR.3, ABR, UBR.1 or UBR.2. This is as defined in ATMF Traffic Management 4.0 specification.

cwspCallFwdPcr.name: cwspCallFwdPcr
cwspCallFwdPcr.description: This object shows the Peak Cell Rate(pcr) in the forward direction of the call.

cwspCallFwdScr.name: cwspCallFwdScr
cwspCallFwdScr.description: This object shows the Sustainable Cell Rate(scr) in the forward direction of the call.

cwspCallFwdMbs.name: cwspCallFwdMbs
cwspCallFwdMbs.description: This object shows the Maximum Burst Size(mbs) of the call in the forward direction.

cwspCallFwdCdvt.name: cwspCallFwdCdvt
cwspCallFwdCdvt.description: This object shows the Cell Delay Variation Tolerance(cdvt) in the forward direction for the call, for PCR and SCR.

cwspCallFwdFrameDiscard.name: cwspCallFwdFrameDiscard
cwspCallFwdFrameDiscard.description: This object shows if the Frame Discard is enabled or disabled in the forward direction for the call

cwspCallBwdConformance.name: cwspCallBwdConformance
cwspCallBwdConformance.description: This object shows the conformance of the call to the traffic sets in the backward direction. It can be CBR.1, CBR.2, CBR.3, VBR.1 VBR.2, VBR.3, ABR, UBR.1 or UBR.2. This is as defined in ATMF Traffic Management 4.0 specification.

cwspCallBwdPcr.name: cwspCallBwdPcr
cwspCallBwdPcr.description: This object shows the Peak Cell Rate in the backward direction of the call.

cwspCallBwdScr.name: cwspCallBwdScr
cwspCallBwdScr.description: This object shows the Sustainable Cell Rate in the backward direction of the call.

cwspCallBwdMbs.name: cwspCallBwdMbs
cwspCallBwdMbs.description: This object shows the Maximum Burst Size of the call in the backward direction.

cwspCallBwdCdvt.name: cwspCallBwdCdvt
cwspCallBwdCdvt.description: This object shows the Cell Delay Variation Tolerance in the backward direction for the call, for PCR and SCR.

cwspCallBwdFrameDiscard.name: cwspCallBwdFrameDiscard
cwspCallBwdFrameDiscard.description: This object shows if the Frame Discard is enabled or disabled in the backward direction for the call.

cwspCallMaxCtd.name: cwspCallMaxCtd
cwspCallMaxCtd.description: This object shows the Maximum Cell Transfer Delay for the call on this interface.

cwspCallMaxFwdCdv.name: cwspCallMaxFwdCdv
cwspCallMaxFwdCdv.description: This object shows the Maximum Cell Delay Variation in the forward direction for this call on this interface.

cwspCallMaxFwdClr.name: cwspCallMaxFwdClr
cwspCallMaxFwdClr.description: This object shows the Maximum Cell Loss Ratio in the forward direction for this call on this interface.

cwspCallMaxBwdCdv.name: cwspCallMaxBwdCdv
cwspCallMaxBwdCdv.description: This object shows the Maximum Cell Delay Variation in the backward direction for this call on this interface.

cwspCallMaxBwdClr.name: cwspCallMaxBwdClr
cwspCallMaxBwdClr.description: This object shows the Maximum Cell Loss Ratio in the backward direction for this call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallTable.name: cwspAbrCallTable
cwspAbrCallTable.description: This table contains information for ABR calls on an interface.

cwspAbrCallEntry.name: cwspAbrCallEntry
cwspAbrCallEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about an ABR call.

cwspAbrCallVpi.name: cwspAbrCallVpi
cwspAbrCallVpi.description: The VPI value of the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallVci.name: cwspAbrCallVci
cwspAbrCallVci.description: The VCI value of the ABR call on this interface. The value should be in the range of 32-65535 (0=SPVP).

cwspAbrCallCallRef.name: cwspAbrCallCallRef
cwspAbrCallCallRef.description: The Call Reference value of the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallClgAddress.name: cwspAbrCallClgAddress
cwspAbrCallClgAddress.description: The Calling Party Address of the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallCldAddress.name: cwspAbrCallCldAddress
cwspAbrCallCldAddress.description: The Called Party Address of the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallClgSubAddr.name: cwspAbrCallClgSubAddr
cwspAbrCallClgSubAddr.description: The Calling Party Subaddress of the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallCldSubAddr.name: cwspAbrCallCldSubAddr
cwspAbrCallCldSubAddr.description: The Called Party Subaddress of the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallOtherIntfIndex.name: cwspAbrCallOtherIntfIndex
cwspAbrCallOtherIntfIndex.description: The Other Interface ID of the ABR call. Generally this would be the outgoing/egress interface for the call.

cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVpi.name: cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVpi
cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVpi.description: The VPI value of the ABR call on the partner interface.

cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVci.name: cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVci
cwspAbrCallOtherIntfVci.description: The VCI value of the ABR call on the partner interface. The value should be in the range of 32-65535 (0=SPVP).

cwspAbrCallOtherIntfCallRef.name: cwspAbrCallOtherIntfCallRef
cwspAbrCallOtherIntfCallRef.description: The Call Reference of the ABR call on the partner interface.

cwspAbrCallType.name: cwspAbrCallType
cwspAbrCallType.description: The Call Type for the ABR call on this interface. The call type could be SVC or SPVC.

cwspAbrCallStartTime.name: cwspAbrCallStartTime
cwspAbrCallStartTime.description: The start time of the ABR call. This is the timestamp when the Setup Message (or Add Party Message) was first received on this interface.

cwspAbrCallBearerClass.name: cwspAbrCallBearerClass
cwspAbrCallBearerClass.description: The Bearer Class of the ABR call. It could be BCOB-A, BCOB-C, BCOB-X or VP Service.

cwspAbrCallServiceCategory.name: cwspAbrCallServiceCategory
cwspAbrCallServiceCategory.description: The Service Category of the ABR call, which is ABR.

cwspAbrCallCastType.name: cwspAbrCallCastType
cwspAbrCallCastType.description: The Cast Type of the ABR call, which can only be Point-to-Point(p2p) call.

cwspAbrCallClipSusceptibility.name: cwspAbrCallClipSusceptibility
cwspAbrCallClipSusceptibility.description: Susceptibility to Clipping. It can be susceptible or not susceptible.

cwspAbrCallFwdConformance.name: cwspAbrCallFwdConformance
cwspAbrCallFwdConformance.description: The Conformance of the ABR call to the traffic sets in the forward direction. It can only be ABR as defined in ATMF Traffic Management 4.0 specification.

cwspAbrCallFwdPcr.name: cwspAbrCallFwdPcr
cwspAbrCallFwdPcr.description: The Peak Cell Rate for the ABR call in the forward direction.

cwspAbrCallFwdMcr.name: cwspAbrCallFwdMcr
cwspAbrCallFwdMcr.description: The Minimum Cell Rate for the ABR call in the forward direction.

cwspAbrCallFwdIcr.name: cwspAbrCallFwdIcr
cwspAbrCallFwdIcr.description: The Initial Cell Rate for the ABR call in the forward direction. This is the rate at which the source starts, both initially and after an idle period. The value must not be larger than PCR, and is usually lower.

cwspAbrCallFwdRif.name: cwspAbrCallFwdRif
cwspAbrCallFwdRif.description: The Rate Increase Factor for the ABR call in the forward direction. This controls the rate at which the rate increases, when a backward RM-cell is received with CI=0 and NI=0. Larger values lead to faster rate increase. The default value is rifOneOver16(12).

cwspAbrCallFwdRdf.name: cwspAbrCallFwdRdf
cwspAbrCallFwdRdf.description: The Rate Decrease Factor for the ABR call in the forward direction. This controls the rate decrease which occurs when backward RM-cells with CI=1, are received. Larger values lead to faster rate decrease. The default value is rdfOneOver16(12).

cwspAbrCallFwdTbe.name: cwspAbrCallFwdTbe
cwspAbrCallFwdTbe.description: The Transient Buffer Exposure for the ABR call in the forward direction. This is the negotiated number of cells that the network would like to limit the source to sending during setup periods, before the first RM-cell returns.

cwspAbrCallFwdNrm.name: cwspAbrCallFwdNrm
cwspAbrCallFwdNrm.description: The Maximum Number of Cells a source may send for each forward RM-cell in the forward direction for the ABR call. The default value is nrm32(5).

cwspAbrCallFwdTrm.name: cwspAbrCallFwdTrm
cwspAbrCallFwdTrm.description: The Upper Bound on the time between forward RM-cells in the forward direction for the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallFwdAdtf.name: cwspAbrCallFwdAdtf
cwspAbrCallFwdAdtf.description: The Allowed Cell Rate (ACR) Decrease Time Factor for the ABR call in the forward direction. This is the time permitted between sending RM-cells before the rate is decreased to ICR. Range is 10 ms to 10.23 seconds. The unit is 10 msecs. For example, the default value of 50 corresponds to a time factor of 500 ms. Larger values allow a source to retain its current rate longer, during periods of relative inactivity. The default is 50 (0.5 seconds).

cwspAbrCallFwdCdf.name: cwspAbrCallFwdCdf
cwspAbrCallFwdCdf.description: The Cutoff Decrease Factor for the ABR call in the forward direction. This controls the decrease in Allowed Cell Rate (ACR) associated with missing RM-cell count (CRM). Larger values result in faster rate decrease. The default value is cdfOneOver16(4).

cwspAbrCallFwdFrameDiscard.name: cwspAbrCallFwdFrameDiscard
cwspAbrCallFwdFrameDiscard.description: Whether Frame Discard is enabled or disabled in the forward direction for the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallBwdPcr.name: cwspAbrCallBwdPcr
cwspAbrCallBwdPcr.description: The Peak Cell Rate for the ABR call in the backward direction.

cwspAbrCallBwdMcr.name: cwspAbrCallBwdMcr
cwspAbrCallBwdMcr.description: The Minimum Cell Rate for the ABR call in the backward direction.

cwspAbrCallBwdIcr.name: cwspAbrCallBwdIcr
cwspAbrCallBwdIcr.description: The Initial Cell Rate for the ABR call in the backward direction. This is the rate at which the source starts, both initially and after an idle period. The value must not be larger than PCR, and is usually lower.

cwspAbrCallBwdRif.name: cwspAbrCallBwdRif
cwspAbrCallBwdRif.description: The Rate Increase Factor for the ABR call in the backward direction. This controls the rate at which the rate increases, when a forward RM-cell is received with CI=0 and NI=0. Larger values lead to faster rate increase. The default value is rifOneOver16(12).

cwspAbrCallBwdRdf.name: cwspAbrCallBwdRdf
cwspAbrCallBwdRdf.description: The Rate Decrease Factor for the ABR call in the backward direction. This controls the rate decrease which occurs when forward RM-cells with CI=1, are received. Larger values lead to faster rate decrease. The default value is rdfOneOver16(12).

cwspAbrCallBwdTbe.name: cwspAbrCallBwdTbe
cwspAbrCallBwdTbe.description: The Transient Buffer Exposure for the ABR call in the backward direction. This is the negotiated number of cells that the network would like to limit the source to sending during setup periods, before the first RM-cell returns.

cwspAbrCallBwdNrm.name: cwspAbrCallBwdNrm
cwspAbrCallBwdNrm.description: The Maximum Number of Cells a source may send for each forward RM-cell in the backward direction for the ABR call. The default value is nrm32(5).

cwspAbrCallBwdTrm.name: cwspAbrCallBwdTrm
cwspAbrCallBwdTrm.description: The Upper Bound on the time between forward RM-cells in the backward direction for the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallBwdAdtf.name: cwspAbrCallBwdAdtf
cwspAbrCallBwdAdtf.description: The Allowed Cell Rate (ACR) Decrease Time Factor for the ABR call in the backward direction. This is the time permitted between sending RM-cells before the rate is decreased to ICR. Range is 10 ms to 10.23 seconds. The unit is 10 msecs. For example, the default value of 50 corresponds to a time factor of 500 ms. Larger values allow a source to retain its current rate longer, during periods of relative inactivity. The default is 50 (0.5 seconds).

cwspAbrCallBwdCdf.name: cwspAbrCallBwdCdf
cwspAbrCallBwdCdf.description: The Cutoff Decrease Factor for the ABR call in the backward direction. This controls the decrease in Allowed Cell Rate (ACR) associated with missing RM-cell count (CRM). Larger values result in faster rate decrease. The default value is cdfOneOver16(4).

cwspAbrCallBwdFrameDiscard.name: cwspAbrCallBwdFrameDiscard
cwspAbrCallBwdFrameDiscard.description: Whether Frame Discard is enabled or disabled in the backward direction for the ABR call.

cwspAbrCallFrtt.name: cwspAbrCallFrtt
cwspAbrCallFrtt.description: The Fixed Round-Trip Time for the ABR call. This is the sum of the fixed and propagation delays from the source to the furthest destination and back.

cwspAbrCallMaxCtd.name: cwspAbrCallMaxCtd
cwspAbrCallMaxCtd.description: The Maximum Cell Transfer Delay for the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallMaxFwdCdv.name: cwspAbrCallMaxFwdCdv
cwspAbrCallMaxFwdCdv.description: The Maximum Cell Delay Variation in the forward direction for the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallMaxFwdClr.name: cwspAbrCallMaxFwdClr
cwspAbrCallMaxFwdClr.description: The Maximum Cell Loss Ratio in the forward direction for the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallMaxBwdCdv.name: cwspAbrCallMaxBwdCdv
cwspAbrCallMaxBwdCdv.description: The Maximum Cell Delay Variation in the backward direction for the ABR call on this interface.

cwspAbrCallMaxBwdClr.name: cwspAbrCallMaxBwdClr
cwspAbrCallMaxBwdClr.description: The Maximum Cell Loss Ratio in the backward direction for the ABR call on this interface.

cwspConnTraceAvail.name: cwspConnTraceAvail
cwspConnTraceAvail.description: This object tells the number of calls can be traced concurrently. Depending on the system resource, this object may vary sometime to time. NMS should query this object to ensure there is system resource available before creating a row in the cwspConnTraceCntlTable.

cwspConnTraceNextIndex.name: cwspConnTraceNextIndex
cwspConnTraceNextIndex.description: When creating a row in the cwspConnTraceCntlTable, NMS should query this object to obtain the index value to be used for row creation.

cwspConnTraceCntlTable.name: cwspConnTraceCntlTable
cwspConnTraceCntlTable.description: This Table contains the objects which control the creation of connection trace for the existing SVC call.

cwspConnTraceCntlEntry.name: cwspConnTraceCntlEntry
cwspConnTraceCntlEntry.description: This object controls the connection trace creation. NMS needs to acquire the next index available to create a row. In addition, NMS needs to provide all read-create objects in the same pdu with RowStatus to be CreateAndGo.

cwspConnTraceIndex.name: cwspConnTraceIndex
cwspConnTraceIndex.description: Index to a row of connection trace.

cwspConnTraceifIndex.name: cwspConnTraceifIndex
cwspConnTraceifIndex.description: The 'ifIndex' indicates the port to a trace connection.

cwspConnTraceSrcVpi.name: cwspConnTraceSrcVpi
cwspConnTraceSrcVpi.description: This object shows the VPI value of the starting point on this interface.

cwspConnTraceSrcVci.name: cwspConnTraceSrcVci
cwspConnTraceSrcVci.description: This object shows The VCI value of the starting point on this interface. The value should be in the range of 32-65535 (0=SPVP).

cwspConnTraceType.name: cwspConnTraceType
cwspConnTraceType.description: Setting this object to either p2p or p2mp to specify tracing a p2p or p2mp connection.

cwspConnTraceCallRef.name: cwspConnTraceCallRef
cwspConnTraceCallRef.description: This object shows the Call Reference value of the call on this interface.

cwspConnTraceLeafRef.name: cwspConnTraceLeafRef
cwspConnTraceLeafRef.description: This object shows the value of the Leaf Reference (EndPointReference) of the Call on this interface, this value is used to support p2mp call trace. For p2p call, this value should be set as 0 by NMS.

cwspConnTraceDestVpi.name: cwspConnTraceDestVpi
cwspConnTraceDestVpi.description: This object shows the endpoint VPI value of the call on this interface.

cwspConnTraceDestVci.name: cwspConnTraceDestVci
cwspConnTraceDestVci.description: This object shows the endpoint VCI value of the call on this interface.

cwspConnTraceDestCallRef.name: cwspConnTraceDestCallRef
cwspConnTraceDestCallRef.description: This object shows the endpoint call reference on this interface.

cwspConnTraceResultStatus.name: cwspConnTraceResultStatus
cwspConnTraceResultStatus.description: This object shows the result of tracing the call. NMS should get positive result (i.e. traceCompleted) for this attribute before query the cwspConnTraceTable.

cwspConnTraceQueryStatus.name: cwspConnTraceQueryStatus
cwspConnTraceQueryStatus.description: This object used to manage rows in this table. However, only CreateAndGo, NotInService, Active, and Destroy are start up the trace. To remove a row, NMS set this value to Destroy. The managed device will either return Active or NotInService.

cwspConnTraceTable.name: cwspConnTraceTable
cwspConnTraceTable.description: This table contains the objects which show the traversed node information in the existing SVC call.

cwspConnTraceEntry.name: cwspConnTraceEntry
cwspConnTraceEntry.description: A conceptual row of the cwspConnTraceTable used to return information about all the nodes belongs to the connection which search criteria is corresponding to instance of the cwspConnTraceCntlTable.

cwspConnTraceDataIndex.name: cwspConnTraceDataIndex
cwspConnTraceDataIndex.description: Along with cwspConnTraceIndex, this object specified an unique entry in the cwspConnTraceTable.

cwspConnTraceNodeId.name: cwspConnTraceNodeId
cwspConnTraceNodeId.description: This octet string represents 22 bytes nodeId in the traced connection.

cwspConnTraceEgressPortId.name: cwspConnTraceEgressPortId
cwspConnTraceEgressPortId.description: This object represents 4 bytes logical port ID of the traversed node. When 0 is specified, the destination node for the trace is reached.

cwspConnTraceEgressVpi.name: cwspConnTraceEgressVpi
cwspConnTraceEgressVpi.description: This object shows the Egress port's VPI value for the traced connection.

cwspConnTraceEgressVci.name: cwspConnTraceEgressVci
cwspConnTraceEgressVci.description: This object shows the Egress port's VCI value for the traced connection

cwspConnTraceEgressCallRef.name: cwspConnTraceEgressCallRef
cwspConnTraceEgressCallRef.description: This object shows the Egress port's call reference.

cwspConnTraceEgressPhyPortId.name: cwspConnTraceEgressPhyPortId
cwspConnTraceEgressPhyPortId.description: This object shows the Egress port's physical port Identifier for the traversed node; if this object is 0 meaning that the destination node for the traced connection has been reached. the meaning for the bytes are: first byte -- flag (used by CLI to decode the rest of bytes ) 2nd byte -- shelf 3rd & 4th bytes -- slot 5th byte -- subslot 6th & 7th bytes -- port 8th byte -- subport

cwspConnTraceLastNode.name: cwspConnTraceLastNode
cwspConnTraceLastNode.description: This value indicates if this entry contains the information about the last node where this trace ends. If it is the last node, this value is 'true(1)' or it is 'false(2)'.

ciscoWANPnniLinkStatus.name: ciscoWANPnniLinkStatus
ciscoWANPnniLinkStatus.description: Indicates the status of a link has changed: 1 - the link entered the 2-Way Inside state, 2 - the link exit the 2-Way Inside state, 3 - the link entered the 2-Way Outside state, 4 - the link exit the 2-Way Outside state. 5 - the link entered the Common Outside state, or 6 - the link exit the Common Outside state and entered the 1-Way Outside state.

ciscoWANPnniPglStatus.name: ciscoWANPnniPglStatus
ciscoWANPnniPglStatus.description: Indicates the status of PGL process has changed: 1 - the PGL exit the hung-election state, or 2 - the PGL entered the hung-election state.

ciscoWANPnniReachability.name: ciscoWANPnniReachability
ciscoWANPnniReachability.description: This object is used in conjunction with ciscoWANPnniRemoteNodeId to indicate the reachability of the RemoteNode has changed: 1 - RemoteNode became reachable, or 2 - RemoteNode became unreachable.

cwspOperUniVersion.name: cwspOperUniVersion
cwspOperUniVersion.description: An indication of the latest version of the ATM Forum UNI Signaling Specification that is supported on this ATM Interface. If this value is not present, a version of the UNI earlier than 3.1 is supported. If the peer IME's value of this object is the same as, or later than the local IME's value, then the version corresponding to the local IME's value should be attempted. Otherwise, if the peer IME's value of this object is earlier, and supported locally, then the local IME should attempt the version corresponding to the peer IME's value. Otherwise, compatibility of the two IMEs cannot be assumed.

cwspOperDeviceType.name: cwspOperDeviceType

An ATM End System shall take the value of user(1), and an ATM network node shall take the value of node(2).

cwspOperIlmiVersion.name: cwspOperIlmiVersion
cwspOperIlmiVersion.description: An indication of the latest version of the ATM Forum ILMI Specification that is supported on this ATM Interface. If the peer IME's value of this object is the same as, or later than the local IME's value, then the version corresponding to the local IME's value should be attempted. Otherwise, if the peer IME's value of this object is earlier, and supported locally, then the local IME should attempt the version corresponding to the peer IME's value. Otherwise, compatibility of the two IMEs cannot be assumed. If this object is not present, a version of the ILMI earlier than 4.0 is supported.

cwspOperNniSigVersion.name: cwspOperNniSigVersion
cwspOperNniSigVersion.description: An indication of the latest version of the ATM Forum PNNI Signaling Specification that is supported on this ATM Interface. Note that the PNNI routing version is not determined through ILMI. If the peer IME's value of this object is the same as, or later than the local IME's value, then the version corresponding to the local IME's value should be attempted. Otherwise, if the peer IME's value of this object is earlier, and supported locally, then the local IME should attempt the version corresponding to the peer IME's value. Otherwise, compatibility of the two IMEs cannot be assumed. Note that 'enni' is not a signaling protocol.
